{{Lunar May}} '''Lunar May''' (旧暦五月) is the fifth {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month|lt_ja=月}} of the year in the {{ill|Japanese Calendar|ja|和暦}} (the {{ill|Lunisolar Calendar|ja|太陰太陽暦}}’s {{ill|Old Lunar Calendar|ja|旧暦}}).
The month that includes the {{ill|Summer Solstice|ja|夏至}} becomes May. In the {{ill|Gregorian Calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} ({{ill|New Calendar|ja|新暦}}), it corresponds approximately to late {{ill|May|ja|5月}} to early {{ill|July|ja|7月}}.
Another name for May is {{reading|'''Satsuki'''|さつき}}. The origin of the name is explained in {{ill|May|ja|5月}}.
In the {{ill|Eastern|ja|東洋}} {{ill|Lunisolar Calendar|ja|太陰太陽暦}}, because the number of days in a month, known as {{ill|Large and Small|ja|大小}} (with large months having 30 days and small months 29 days), varies each year, there are years in which May ends on the 29th and May 30th does not exist.
