{{Lunisolar May}} '''Lunisolar May''' (旧暦五月) is the fifth {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month|lt_ja=月|12=draft|12=draft}} of the year in the {{ill|Japanese Calendar|ja|和暦|12=draft|12=draft}} (the {{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|太陰太陽暦|12=draft|12=draft}}’s {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft}}).
The month that includes the {{ill|Summer Solstice|ja|夏至|12=draft|12=draft}} becomes May. In the {{ill|Gregorian Calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|New Calendar|ja|新暦|1=New Calendar (Japan)|lt=New Calendar|12=draft|12=draft}}), it corresponds approximately to late {{ill|May|ja|5月|12=draft|12=draft}} to early {{ill|July|ja|7月|12=draft|12=draft}}.
Another name for May is {{nihongo|'''Satsuki'''|さつき}}. The origin of the name is explained in {{ill|May|ja|5月|12=draft|12=draft}}.
In the {{ill|Eastern|ja|東洋|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|太陰太陽暦|12=draft|12=draft}}, because the number of days in a month, known as {{ill|Large and Small|ja|大小|12=draft|12=draft}} (with large months having 30 days and small months 29 days), varies each year, there are years in which May ends on the 29th and May 30th does not exist.
