{{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''Lunisolar May''' (旧暦五月) is the fifth {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month|lt_ja=月|qq=}} of the year in the {{ill|Japanese Calendar|ja|和暦|qq=}} (the {{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|太陰太陽暦|1=Lunisolar calendar|2=ja|3=太陰太陽暦|comment=note that this is not the Japanese lunisolar calendar it is any lunisolar calendar|4=ru|5=Лунно-солнечный календарь|6=de|7=Lunisolarkalender|8=es|9=Calendario lunisolar|10=fr|11=Calendrier luni-solaire|qq=}}’s {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}).
The month that includes the {{ill|Summer Solstice|ja|夏至|qq=}} becomes May. In the {{ill|Gregorian Calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} ({{ill|New Calendar|ja|新暦|1=New Calendar (Japan)|lt=New Calendar|qq=}}), it corresponds approximately to late {{ill|May|ja|5月|qq=}} to early {{ill|July|ja|7月|qq=}}.
Another name for May is {{nihongo|'''Satsuki'''|さつき|qq=}}. The origin of the name is explained in {{ill|May|ja|5月|qq=}}.
In the {{ill|Eastern|ja|東洋|qq=}} {{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|太陰太陽暦|1=Lunisolar calendar|2=ja|3=太陰太陽暦|comment=note that this is not the Japanese lunisolar calendar it is any lunisolar calendar|4=ru|5=Лунно-солнечный календарь|6=de|7=Lunisolarkalender|8=es|9=Calendario lunisolar|10=fr|11=Calendrier luni-solaire|qq=}}, because the number of days in a month, known as {{ill|Large and Small|ja|大小|qq=}} (with large months having 30 days and small months 29 days), varies each year, there are years in which May ends on the 29th and May 30th does not exist.
